"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# Indexer API\\n\\nThe Indexer is a high-availability system designed to provide structured data. It serves both over its [HTTP/REST API](/indexer-client/http) for spontaneous requests and over its [WebSockets API](/indexer-client/websockets) for continuous data streaming.\\n\\nSee the [guide](/interaction/endpoints#indexer-client) on how to use the available Indexer client to learn how to connect to it.\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/indexer-client#indexer-api\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>The Indexer is a high-availability system designed to provide structured data. It serves both over its <a href=\\\"/indexer-client/http\\\">HTTP/REST API</a> for spontaneous requests and over its <a href=\\\"/indexer-client/websockets\\\">WebSockets API</a> for continuous data streaming.</p>\\n<p>See the <a href=\\\"/interaction/endpoints#indexer-client\\\">guide</a> on how to use the available Indexer client to learn how to connect to it.</p>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/indexer-client/#indexer-api\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nThe Indexer is a high-availability system designed to provide structured data. It serves both over its HTTP/REST API for spontaneous requests and over its WebSockets API for continuous data streaming.\\nSee the guide on how to use the available Indexer client to learn how to connect to it.\",\"title\":\"Indexer API\",\"titles\":[]}]}}"
